[SCENIC_ROUTING.md](mdc:SCENIC_ROUTING.md)

Prioritize:
- 2 lane roads
- "secondary" roads
- roads with speed limit 45-65mph
- contiguous routing

De-prioritize:
- roads that are not twisty


Exclude altogether:
- unpaved roads
- roads less than 2 lanes
- any waypoint that causes retracing our steps (out-and-back). loops are allowed but not retracing steps.

Filtering mechanism:
- use OSM meta data about the street characteristics to drive our logic
- do NOT use the names of streets as part of the logic

Implementation (graph-based routing):
- `roadGraph.ts` builds a topology graph from raw Overpass data: ways are
  split into edges at shared junction nodes; hard exclusions (unpaved,
  <2 lanes, tracks, private access) never enter the graph.
- `graphRouter.ts` runs Dijkstra with profile-specific edge costs: desirable
  edges (twisty, secondary, 2-lane, 45-65mph) cost less than their length,
  undesirable edges cost more. Dijkstra never revisits a node, so retracing
  steps is impossible by construction.
- `graphRouteGenerator.ts` emits evenly spaced pin waypoints along the chosen
  path so Google Maps follows the selected roads, then fetches real
  directions per route option.
